WEBVTT

00:21.982 --> 00:24.234
Gentleman Ghost picked a good night
for this caper.

00:25.402 --> 00:26.486
[HORSE NEIGHING]

00:34.244 --> 00:38.331
GENTLEMAN GHOST: You will not
take me away in chains again, Batman.

00:46.506 --> 00:48.216
[GENTLEMAN GHOST SHOUTS]

00:53.596 --> 00:54.889
[YELLING]

01:03.940 --> 01:05.358
Forget the money.

01:05.358 --> 01:07.235
Got it. Save the money.

01:09.029 --> 01:11.197
Oh, beautiful dinero.

01:11.448 --> 01:12.949
Moola. Simoleons.

01:13.199 --> 01:14.409
Dough, re, mi. Cabbage.

01:30.258 --> 01:31.384
[HORSE NEIGHING]

01:38.767 --> 01:40.393
GENTLEMAN GHOST:
And now, Batman...

01:40.643 --> 01:43.563
...I invite you to join me in the afterlife.

01:46.357 --> 01:47.400
[GENTLEMAN GHOST GRUNTS]

01:50.153 --> 01:54.449
FIRE: Didn't your mother tell you
never to play with fire?

02:05.335 --> 02:06.711
Nth metal knuckles.

02:12.425 --> 02:14.010
And Nth metal cuffs.

02:14.260 --> 02:15.887
It's a winning combination.

02:16.137 --> 02:19.349
Not even you can phase through those,
Craddock.

02:20.391 --> 02:22.185
Thanks for the assist, Fire.

02:22.435 --> 02:24.437
Nice work, team.

02:24.437 --> 02:26.106
Ooh. Hello, sugar.

02:26.356 --> 02:28.441
Ahem. Where is it?

02:28.691 --> 02:29.859
Where is what, Bats?

02:30.110 --> 02:31.111
The money.

02:31.361 --> 02:33.780
Oh, yeah, the money.

02:36.449 --> 02:38.493
- The rest of it.
- Oh, come on.

02:38.785 --> 02:40.787
No finder's fee?

02:43.331 --> 02:44.666
Now, that's all of it.

02:44.916 --> 02:46.209
Cross my heart and hope to--

02:46.459 --> 02:47.418
[BELCHES]

03:49.314 --> 03:50.106
MAN:
Look.

03:50.398 --> 03:52.066
What is that?

03:57.322 --> 03:58.740
[ROARING]

03:59.157 --> 04:00.200
[BOTH GASP]

04:00.200 --> 04:01.868
[SHOUTS]

04:02.660 --> 04:03.995
[ALL SHOUTING]

04:10.418 --> 04:12.670
Your clay is done, humans.

04:12.921 --> 04:15.757
The age of the ape is at hand.

04:18.676 --> 04:19.761
[SCREAMING]

04:29.062 --> 04:30.230
[GRUNTS]

04:30.772 --> 04:31.814
[SCREAMING]

04:36.486 --> 04:37.737
PLASTIC MAN:
Come on, Bats.

04:37.987 --> 04:39.239
I made a mistake.

04:39.489 --> 04:41.199
One tiny little mistake.

04:41.449 --> 04:44.285
You were trying to keep
that stolen money for yourself.

04:44.285 --> 04:46.955
Well, yeah. But give me a break,
will you?

04:47.205 --> 04:49.332
I stuck my neck out for you, O'Brian.

04:49.582 --> 04:52.335
With the judge, the parole board,
the League.

04:52.585 --> 04:54.587
How long are you gonna hold that over me?

04:54.879 --> 04:58.508
You know, I didn't ask you to help me out.
What, are you my dad or something?

04:58.800 --> 05:02.095
You're not the boss of me. Batman, if I wanted
to feel guilty, I could call my mom--

05:02.387 --> 05:04.222
BATMAN:
Just a tap of my finger.

05:04.472 --> 05:06.015
[BEEPING]

05:08.559 --> 05:10.186
Distress signal. Hang on.

05:20.196 --> 05:21.322
[GROWLS]

05:23.408 --> 05:25.451
These results are unacceptable.

05:25.702 --> 05:29.622
My e-ray needs a few more adjustments.

05:32.000 --> 05:33.376
Experiment's over.

05:33.668 --> 05:38.256
Let's get the spoils back to base
and appropriate their finer accoutrements.

06:02.113 --> 06:03.197
Batman.

06:03.948 --> 06:06.701
The one human worthy of my intellect.

06:06.951 --> 06:12.123
Your appearance is inconvenient,
but I relish the challenge.

06:19.088 --> 06:20.798
Are you seeing what I'm seeing?

06:21.049 --> 06:23.134
Because I'm seeing gorillas
riding pterodactyls...

06:23.384 --> 06:26.137
...with harpoon guns. Stealing a boat.

06:26.137 --> 06:27.263
It's Gorilla Grodd.

06:27.513 --> 06:29.390
It's messed up, is what it is.

07:06.511 --> 07:08.638
GORILLA GRODD:
You are under my control.

07:08.930 --> 07:12.475
You cannot resist
the power of my superior mind.

07:12.767 --> 07:15.061
Succumb to Grodd.

07:17.188 --> 07:18.314
[BEEPING]

07:18.564 --> 07:20.316
Bats. Bats?

07:21.984 --> 07:23.861
Hey, snap out of it, Bats.

07:24.112 --> 07:26.197
<i>Batsy? Bats? Woo-hoe.</i>

07:26.197 --> 07:27.407
Bats, wake up, buddy.

07:29.992 --> 07:31.536
Bats!

07:40.545 --> 07:43.381
Hmm. A bit too easy for my taste.

08:06.070 --> 08:07.071
Dinosaur Island.

08:07.321 --> 08:09.615
A mysterious land
that exists outside of time...

08:09.866 --> 08:12.326
...where the normal laws of nature
don't apply.

08:12.326 --> 08:13.578
What makes you say that?

08:13.828 --> 08:15.580
The dinosaur.

08:16.414 --> 08:17.582
[ROARING]

08:25.214 --> 08:26.507
[ROARING]

08:37.310 --> 08:38.561
[SCREAMING]

08:41.147 --> 08:44.358
Hey! Stop it! Oh! Hey!

08:49.447 --> 08:52.408
Ew, dinosaur germs.

08:56.204 --> 08:58.289
Hang on, Bats. I'm coming.

09:03.461 --> 09:05.213
Grab on.

09:20.353 --> 09:21.854
Man, this place is insane.

09:22.104 --> 09:24.941
An island full of dinosaurs?
Wish I had my camera.

09:28.694 --> 09:31.697
What, you're not still mad
about the money thing, are you?

09:31.989 --> 09:33.950
Oh, come on. Give me another chance.

09:34.200 --> 09:36.160
Tell me one reason why I should.

09:36.410 --> 09:40.623
Because it's your fault
I became Plastic Man in the first place.

09:41.624 --> 09:44.001
You remember, don't you, Bats?

09:47.713 --> 09:52.218
I was a lowlife crook named Eel O'Brian
working in Kite Man's gang.

09:52.885 --> 09:55.012
Even I didn't deserve
what happened that night.

09:59.100 --> 10:00.643
Jig's up, Kite Man.

10:22.790 --> 10:23.916
[GROANS]

10:24.166 --> 10:25.751
[SCREAMING]

10:29.422 --> 10:31.882
[GASPING]

10:34.260 --> 10:37.680
Those chemicals turned me
into the freak I am today.

10:37.680 --> 10:40.683
The only reason you ever helped me
is because you feel guilty.

10:40.933 --> 10:43.686
There are no happy endings
to a life of crime, O'Brian.

10:43.686 --> 10:45.229
You made your choice.

10:45.479 --> 10:47.690
It's up to you to make the best of it.

10:57.742 --> 10:59.619
Grodd's hideout.

11:05.708 --> 11:08.127
Look at all those luxury yachts.

11:08.377 --> 11:10.755
Grodd must have stolen a fortune.

11:11.422 --> 11:14.300
And I bet it's all stashed in there.

11:14.550 --> 11:17.470
We are here to stop
whatever Grodd has planned.

11:17.720 --> 11:18.888
Don't get any funny ideas.

11:19.138 --> 11:20.765
Oh, no, I'm cool.

11:21.015 --> 11:23.225
Let's go. We're taking Grodd down.

11:23.476 --> 11:25.269
- Hard.
- Not so fast.

11:25.519 --> 11:29.774
Grodd will have this whole valley
wired with cameras, tripwires and sensors.

11:30.107 --> 11:33.361
They didn't call me The Eel for nothing.

11:33.944 --> 11:35.738
Try to keep up, huh?

11:52.838 --> 11:55.007
Oh, yeah. The Eel.

11:55.257 --> 11:56.926
[BEEPING]

11:57.176 --> 11:58.969
[ALARM WAILING]

12:17.822 --> 12:20.491
You're a long way
from Gorilla City, Grodd.

12:20.741 --> 12:26.414
Dinosaur Island's unique inhabitants
will be the vanguard of a new civilization.

12:26.664 --> 12:28.749
A glorious gorilla nation.

12:28.999 --> 12:32.962
A utopia that will spread
to claim the entire world.

12:35.089 --> 12:39.635
My e-ray evolves humans
into their ultimate expression.

12:39.885 --> 12:41.595
The intelligent ape.

12:41.846 --> 12:44.598
It only requires one more test.

12:44.890 --> 12:47.977
And I see two volunteers.

12:48.644 --> 12:49.645
Not interested.

12:50.062 --> 12:51.564
[GRUNTS]

13:02.366 --> 13:04.410
Don't bother with the mind control,
Grodd.

13:04.660 --> 13:07.246
I'm blocking it
with a technique I learned in Tibet.

13:10.040 --> 13:11.375
[GROANING]

13:32.396 --> 13:36.150
I am the superior being.

13:36.400 --> 13:37.943
Bats, no!

13:38.194 --> 13:39.570
[SCREAMING]

13:44.742 --> 13:47.828
Send out a search party.

13:52.708 --> 13:54.502
<i>Nice going, Has.</i>

13:54.794 --> 13:59.048
Way to get one of your only friends
in this lousy world captured.

14:04.011 --> 14:06.806
[GASPING]

14:09.975 --> 14:11.477
[GROANING]

14:17.608 --> 14:18.818
[EKG BEEPING]

14:25.825 --> 14:28.661
O'BRIAN: Kite Man planned the whole thing,
Your Honor.

14:29.036 --> 14:30.996
JUDGE:
Take him away.

14:33.457 --> 14:38.128
MAN: Eel O'Brian, why should
this parole board show you leniency?

14:38.379 --> 14:39.463
BATMAN:
I'll give you my word.

14:39.713 --> 14:43.843
I'll take full responsibility
for O'Brian's rehabilitation.

14:54.687 --> 14:56.480
Hang in there, Bats.

14:56.772 --> 14:59.650
I swear I won't let you down again.

15:06.448 --> 15:07.616
[GROANING]

15:10.995 --> 15:12.162
GORILLA GRODD:
Good.

15:12.413 --> 15:13.789
You're awake.

15:16.208 --> 15:18.544
You amuse me, Batman.

15:18.878 --> 15:20.838
You dress as an animal.

15:20.838 --> 15:23.716
You battle
against the worst of humanity.

15:23.966 --> 15:28.846
The vile underbelly
that only wishes to destroy.

15:28.846 --> 15:31.765
You should join my noble cause.

15:32.016 --> 15:34.768
My only cause
is to send you back to the zoo.

15:35.811 --> 15:36.979
[GRUNTING]

15:37.229 --> 15:39.189
Prepare the e-ray.

15:39.481 --> 15:40.816
[E-RAY POWERING UP]

15:51.035 --> 15:53.621
Not gonna let you down, Bats.

15:55.623 --> 15:56.665
[GROANS]

16:04.673 --> 16:05.841
On my way, pal.

16:05.841 --> 16:07.384
[GASPS]

16:11.847 --> 16:13.724
Just a slight delay, Bats.

16:17.853 --> 16:20.522
Oh, boy. This is not happening.
This is not happening!

16:20.773 --> 16:24.526
GORILLA GRODD:
Humanity is an evolutionary dead end.

16:24.777 --> 16:27.655
A species determined to destroy itself...

16:27.905 --> 16:30.699
and take the rest of the planet with it.

16:30.950 --> 16:36.872
My species represents the first
of a new biological paradigm.

16:37.164 --> 16:41.627
We have transcended
the animal kingdom.

16:43.087 --> 16:45.339
BATMAN:
Missed a spot.

16:48.300 --> 16:49.635
[GRUNTING]

16:49.885 --> 16:51.095
Seize him!

17:02.606 --> 17:05.776
Why does this kind of stuff
never happen to Superman?

17:13.867 --> 17:15.828
Not gonna let you get turned into--

17:15.828 --> 17:17.705
Hello.

17:19.748 --> 17:21.834
No. Stay strong, O'Brian.

17:22.042 --> 17:23.877
Not gonna let Batman down.

17:24.128 --> 17:25.671
Not gonna--

17:30.718 --> 17:33.804
Hee! I'm on my way, buddy.

17:37.808 --> 17:40.769
Gonna be there in just one second, okay?

17:49.695 --> 17:51.947
PLASTIC MAN:
I got your back, Bats.

17:52.197 --> 17:53.782
Told you I wouldn't let you clown.

17:55.242 --> 17:56.535
[GROANING]

17:57.036 --> 17:58.746
[GROANS]

18:03.542 --> 18:06.628
I've finally outsmarted the Batman.

18:10.966 --> 18:14.136
What?
Like you don't look like a freak too?

18:17.056 --> 18:18.265
[GULPS]

18:18.557 --> 18:20.934
Tell me you've got a plan, Bat-- Ape.

18:20.934 --> 18:23.520
I always have a plan.

18:28.192 --> 18:30.152
COMPUTER:
Five minutes to wave pulse.

18:30.402 --> 18:31.487
Hear that?

18:31.737 --> 18:33.572
In less than 300 seconds...

18:33.822 --> 18:39.036
...this device will bathe everything
in a 500-mile radius with e-rays.

18:39.036 --> 18:42.164
Everyone in the Bahamas, West Indies...

18:42.414 --> 18:46.710
...and even Florida will evolve.

18:58.180 --> 18:59.598
Bad monkey.

19:02.851 --> 19:04.478
No, you don't.

19:25.040 --> 19:27.167
I can't believe I'm doing this.

20:00.450 --> 20:01.827
[GROANING]

20:07.499 --> 20:10.752
COMPUTER: "Ten, nine, eight..."
- Too late, Batman.

20:11.003 --> 20:14.339
COMPUTER: Seven, six, five...

20:14.590 --> 20:18.552
...four, three, two, one.

20:20.095 --> 20:21.680
No

20:30.772 --> 20:32.191
[ALL GROANING]

21:08.560 --> 21:09.519
Human?

21:09.811 --> 21:12.481
No! No! No!

21:12.731 --> 21:15.484
I reversed the matrix emitter
when Grodd wasn't looking.

21:22.866 --> 21:26.078
Looks like human ingenuity
beats ape intellect once again.

21:26.787 --> 21:27.996
[snow-me]

21:33.168 --> 21:36.755
Look, I rounded up every last jewel.
You wanna count them?

21:38.090 --> 21:39.383
No.

21:39.675 --> 21:42.594
Ha, ha. What? Seriously?

21:42.886 --> 21:44.388
I trust you.

21:44.930 --> 21:46.223
You sure about that?

21:59.903 --> 22:03.824
GORILLA GRODD:
No mere prison of iron and stone...

22:04.074 --> 22:10.038
...can contain the most brilliant mind
the world has ever seen.

22:10.038 --> 22:14.209
My intellect may be refined,
but my revenge--

22:14.501 --> 22:18.922
My revenge will be as savage
as the darkest jungle.
